-- Indian shares snap four-day winning streak on profit-taking 
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Wed May 14, 2014 06:12AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 14 (Reuters) - Indian shares retreated from record highs hit a day earlier, snapping a four-session winning streak as investors booked profits in blue-chips such as HDFC Bank <HDBK.NS> ahead of the release of election results on Friday.

HDFC Bank provisionally fell 1.71 percent after hitting a record high of 800 rupees on Tuesday, while Reliance Industries <RELI.NS> fell 1.74 percent.